## Distributed Data Processing Framework (Liang)

* Wrote a peer-to-peer model parallel engine and data parallel engine, then wrapped them in a separate core module
  - the p2p model turned out to be more complicated that the map reduce and parameter server models.
* Implemented a stochastic gradient decedent algorithm using the model parallel engine
* Investigated and implemented an Latent Dirichelet Analysis (LDA) model on top of the P2P engine (after much debugging!)
* Implemented a simple DHT for the framework

Established two interesting directions for research questions related to the data framework:
- Barrier control
- Model consistency
